complete the experiment.

526
00:30:06,300 --> 00:30:07,800
He's going to up her dosage.

527
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:10,157
If we don't find diana soon, she's going to wind up
in the same shape as kevin.

528
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:16,328
I think, it's the silence that's messing us up.

529
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:18,007
It's too awkward.

530
00:30:18,300 --> 00:30:19,868
So instead of us just staring
at each other,

531
00:30:19,869 --> 00:30:21,784
i thought we'll talk.

532
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:25,100
Okay. Um...

533
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:27,600
is there something specific
you wanted to talk about?

534
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:28,700
No.

535
00:30:28,700 --> 00:30:31,100
You pick.

536
00:30:31,100 --> 00:30:34,300
Well, i've been thinking about
my parents a lot lately,

537
00:30:34,300 --> 00:30:37,200
What they'd think
of all this,

538
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:39,000
This place...

539
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,700
Me,

540
00:30:41,700 --> 00:30:45,100
Sitting here trying to
figure out how to use my...

541
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:47,500
Telekinetic ability?

542
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:50,200
You know, you can
say it out loud.

543
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:52,200
It's nothing
to be embarrassed about.

544
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:54,300
Yeah, you can say that,

545
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:58,600
But when i first got back,
i was a 4400,

546
00:30:58,600 --> 00:31:00,200
But i didn't have
an ability.

547
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:03,000
I felt normal.

548
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,300
It was something
i could hold on to.

549
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:07,850
Now you have to get used to the idea
that you're special.

550
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:10,960
Is that what my parents
would thinkif they were here?

551
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:14,254
Or would they just think that their son
had become a freak?

552
00:31:17,700 --> 00:31:19,600
Richard.

553
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:22,600
When you got taken,

554
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:24,100
you were one of
the first black pilots

555
00:31:24,100 --> 00:31:25,900
in all of the military.

556
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:27,700
You were at the vanguard.

557
00:31:27,700 --> 00:31:31,700
Now you're part of
a different vanguard.

558
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:34,800
There's a reason
they picked you.

559
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:37,900
I think your parents
would be proud.

560
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:40,400
Yeah.

561
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:42,000
Uh...

562
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,400
Maybe that's true.

563
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,200
Richard?

564
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,600
Whoa.

565
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:04,200
Well, i guess
that worked, huh?

566
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:21,200
This will be fine.

567
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:23,200
We can work here
for a while.

568
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,865
Tell him he can go home.

569
00:32:25,500 --> 00:32:26,451
Please.

570
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:28,000
You have to help me.

571
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,300
Say something.

572
00:32:29,300 --> 00:32:30,500
Don't bother.

573
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:33,300
He's not going to remember
any of this.

574
00:32:33,300 --> 00:32:35,500
Thank you.

575
00:32:35,500 --> 00:32:37,300
You can
go home now.

576
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,500
Kevin?

577
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:41,700
Can i get you
some water?

578
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:44,100
I'm fine.

579
00:32:44,100 --> 00:32:46,000
Kevin.

580
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,700
You're dying.

581
00:32:47,700 --> 00:32:49,200
You're killing yourself.

582
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:50,754
And now you're going to kill me, too.

583
00:32:52,500 --> 00:32:54,700
No.

584
00:32:54,700 --> 00:32:58,500
You will not die.

585
00:32:58,500 --> 00:33:02,064
My work... is valid.

586
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,900
Are you sure?

587
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:05,100
Look at yourself.

588
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:08,285
If it isn't working in me,

589
00:33:08,300 --> 00:33:10,550
the fault isn't
with the experiment.

590
00:33:10,551 --> 00:33:11,400
It's with me.

591
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:16,973
All those years, the shock treatments,
the fistfuls of medications,

592
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:18,200
they must have changed me.

593
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,900
I'm not a good subject.

594
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:23,800
There is no good subject.

595
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:26,700
Kevin, you're brilliant,
but you're wrong.

596
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:30,710
You failed, and you're notthinking clearly enough
to see that.

597
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:37,341
My mind is not compromised.

598
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,600
We are at a point, Diana,

599
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:43,700
Where it would be easy
for the timid to turn back.

600
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:45,600
We have to be braver
than that.

601
00:33:47,500 --> 00:33:49,500
And, if necessary...

602
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:52,300
Oh. No...

603
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:58,600
Oh...

604
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:01,381
i'm prepared to be brave enough
for both of us.

605
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:15,000
Working on a song?

606
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,100
The end of one.

607
00:34:16,100 --> 00:34:17,460
Can't nail it, though.

608
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:24,900
Inspiration.

609
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:29,100
Are you shocked
i'm drinking my lunch?

610
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:30,200
I didn't say anything.

611
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:32,000
Good, because this is...

612
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:34,400
listen...

613
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:38,800
this here is called
"maintaining a base level."

614
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:46,500
That's kind of scary, actually.

615
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:48,400
Shawn.

616
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,600
Don't worry.

617
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:52,900
I've made a solemn vow
not to over-indulge...

618
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:54,900
unless, of course,
you're around.

619
00:34:54,900 --> 00:34:59,300
Yeah, that's kind of the thing.

620
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:03,400
You're not going to be around,
is that it?

621
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:06,700
You're not coming on the road?

622
00:35:07,900 --> 00:35:09,600
I wanted to.

623
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,700
It's just...

624
00:35:11,700 --> 00:35:14,300
you know, even if it was
for a little while.

625
00:35:14,300 --> 00:35:16,500
This gift i have, though,

626
00:35:16,500 --> 00:35:19,700
it's kind of
a responsibility, you know?

627
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:22,100
And i don't mean
to be harsh, man,

628
00:35:22,100 --> 00:35:24,900
but i don't think
it was meant to be used

629
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:28,599
As a rock star's personal safety net.

630
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:42,400
You don't know that.

631
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:47,800
Maybe they sent you back
to keep me alive

632
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:50,400
So i could finish my album.

633
00:35:53,100 --> 00:35:56,900
Nick, if you go down again...

634
00:35:58,300 --> 00:36:00,293
i can't be there for you.

635
00:36:35,700 --> 00:36:38,500
There's still time,
you know.

636
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:39,900
We can save him.

637
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,800
I think maybe you don't have
enough faith in kevin.

638
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:45,200
He can do this.

639
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,700
He's special.

640
00:36:46,700 --> 00:36:48,600
That's why
they had me wake him up.

641
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:49,700
Tess?

642
00:36:50,700 --> 00:36:53,000
I packed an adrenaline shot
when we left the cabin.

643
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,400
Have you seen it?

644
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,500
No.

645
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,400
I need it.

646
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:01,400
It has to be here
in case i slip under.

647
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,400
Ah.
Kevin?

648
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:08,700
I think i got stung
by a bee.

649
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,600
What is this?

650
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:23,000
Don't move, dr. Burkhoff!

651
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,400
- Tess?
- There'snowhere to go.

652
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:25,900
We've got this place
surrounded.

653
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:29,600
Nobody fire.

654
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:32,000
He's not going anywhere.

655
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,500
Diana,
are you all right?

656
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:34,600
Tom.

657
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,900
Whoa.
Hold still, burkhoff.

658
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:47,100
Put your hands up.

659
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:53,000
Burkhoff!

660
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:29,500
They won't be able
to hide for long.

661
00:38:29,900 --> 00:38:32,000
Tess will run out of meds.

662
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,300
Dr. Burkhoff
is not exactly inconspicuous.

663
00:38:34,300 --> 00:38:35,715
They'll show themselves,
we'll find them.

664
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:39,200
You mean we'll find tess.

665
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:41,100
It doesn't sound like
burkhoff will live out the week.

666
00:38:41,100 --> 00:38:43,100
I don't get it.

667
00:38:43,100 --> 00:38:45,045
He was supposed to be
the father of 4400 technology.

668
00:38:45,046 --> 00:38:46,020
That's why they woke him up.

669
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:48,500
Well, that's
just our theory.

670
00:38:48,500 --> 00:38:50,200
Maybe you're putting
too much faith in the future.

671
00:38:55,100 --> 00:38:57,200
Diana's okay?

672
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,400
Yeah,
she'll get there.

673
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:01,800
She's down
in ntac medical.

674
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:44,400
You got us a ride.

675
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:47,500
Someone
let me borrow them.

676
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:12,671
Mr. Ryland wants a status report
on the promicin.

677
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:13,800
We're good.

678
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:14,800
Great, actually.

679
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:17,743
We have enough of a stockpile to last us
for almost two years.

